    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "**District Policy on Cell Phone Use**  \n*Effective Date: [Insert Date]*  \n\n**1. Permitted Use**  \nCell phones may be used by students for essential communication with parents or guardians and for emergency situations only. This includes calls, texts, or messages that require immediate response, such as reporting a medical emergency, providing transportation, or addressing critical school safety matters.  \n\n**2. Prohibited Use**  \nDuring instructional time, cell phones are prohibited from being used for non-essential purposes, including social media, gaming, or entertainment. Phones must be turned off or placed in a designated storage area during class, assemblies, and other school activities unless otherwise authorized.  \n\n*To address the issue of hidden devices, the following measures are added to the Prohibited Use section:*  \n\n- **No Hidden Use:** Students are strictly prohibited from keeping cell phones in their pockets, under desks, or in any other concealed location during class. All devices must be visibly stored in the designated locker or bag area.  \n- **Teacher Visibility:** Teachers will be empowered to conduct random checks of student devices during lessons, and any device found in a concealed spot will be treated as a policy violation.  \n- **Accountability:** If a student is caught",
